                </button>
            </div>
            
            <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--glacier-blue);margin-bottom:0.8rem;">Core Research Themes</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                <li>Aerosol–snow interaction and snow albedo reduction over the Western Himalayas.</li>
                <li>Field-based atmospheric and cryospheric measurements in high-altitude Himalayan sites.</li>
                <li>Aerosol optical and microphysical properties during dust storms and polluted events.</li>
                <li>Ice-nucleating particles and their role in cloud microphysics and regional climate.</li>
                <li>Remote sensing and spatial analysis of atmospheric and cryospheric parameters.</li>
                <li>Climate change impacts on glaciers and snow cover in mountain regions.</li>
                <li>Statistical and machine-learning-based environmental data analysis.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--glacier-blue);margin-bottom:0.8rem;">Fieldwork & Campaign Experience</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left:1.5rem;">
                <li>Multi-season field campaigns in the Western Himalayas, including snow sampling up to ~5000 m, glacier treks, and in situ measurements of aerosols and snow properties.</li>
                <li>Deployment and calibration of nephelometer, aethalometer, SMPS, OPC, sun photometer, and related radiometric instruments under challenging field conditions.</li>
                <li>Logistics and safety coordination for remote glacier expeditions and high-elevation sampling campaigns.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

